1
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:15,015
ONE DEGREE
TO OVERLAP.

2
00:00:16,141 --> 00:00:18,727
STAND BY TO PHOTOGRAPH.

3
00:00:23,899 --> 00:00:26,025
NOW.

4
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,952
[SIGHS]

5
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,454
THREE DAYS
OF THIS NOW, SIR.

6
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:40,791
OTHER SHIPS MUST HAVE
MADE STAR MAPS
OF SOME OF THIS.

7
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:43,502
NEGATIVE,
LIEUTENANT.

8
00:00:43,627 --> 00:00:45,546
WE ARE THE FIRST
TO REACH THIS FAR.

9
00:00:45,671 --> 00:00:47,965
[BEEPING]

10
00:00:48,089 --> 00:00:50,009
SIR, CONTACT
WITH AN OBJECT.

11
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,176
IT'S MOVING
TOWARD US.

12
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:52,845
NO VISUAL
CONTACT YET.

13
00:00:52,970 --> 00:00:54,638
DEFLECTORS,
FULL INTENSITY.

14
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:55,764
IT'S COMING
AT LIGHT SPEED.

15
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:56,974
COLLISION COURSE.

16
00:00:57,098 --> 00:00:59,768
EVASIVE MANEUVERS,
MR. SULU.

17
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:02,688
OBJECT CHANGING DIRECTION,
TOO, SIR.

18
00:01:02,813 --> 00:01:05,106
KEEPS COMING AT US.

19
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:08,569
I'M GETTING NO SIGNAL
FROM IT, SIR.

20
00:01:08,694 --> 00:01:10,571
STILL COLLISION COURSE.

21
00:01:10,696 --> 00:01:12,656
DEFLECTORS AREN'T
STOPPING IT.

22
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,157
SOUND ALARM.

23
00:01:14,282 --> 00:01:15,910
IT'S SLOWING DOWN,
MR. SPOCK.

24
00:01:16,035 --> 00:01:17,327
COUNTERMAND ALARM.

25
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,246
ALL ENGINES FULL STOP.

26
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,791
VISUAL CONTACT.

27
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,027
AHEAD SLOW.

28
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:52,237
STEER A COURSE
AROUND IT, MR. SULU.

29
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:19,890
IT'S BLOCKING THE WAY!

30
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:22,225
QUITE UNNECESSARY TO RAISE
YOUR VOICE, MR. BAILEY.

31
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,311
ALL ENGINES STOP.

32
00:02:24,436 --> 00:02:25,479
SOUND THE ALERT.

33
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:30,150
BRIDGE TO ALL DECKS--
CONDITION ALERT.

34
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:33,403
ALL DECKS--
CONDITION ALERT.

35
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,781
CAPTAIN KIRK
TO THE BRIDGE.

36
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:45,916
SPACE...
THE FINAL FRONTIER.

37
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:50,129
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

38
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,380
ITS FIVE-YEAR MISSION

39
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:55,467
TO EXPLORE
STRANGE NEW WORLDS...

40
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:58,679
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE
AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS...

41
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:03,892
TO BOLDLY GO WHERE
NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.

42
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:40,428
Kirk: CAPTAIN'S LOG,
STARDATE 1512.2.

43
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,305
ON OUR THIRD DAY
OF STAR MAPPING,

44
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,516
AN UNEXPLAINED
CUBICAL OBJECT

45
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,267
BLOCKED OUR VESSEL'S PATH.

46
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:49,730
ON THE BRIDGE,
MR. SPOCK IMMEDIATELY
ORDERED GENERAL ALERT.

47
00:03:49,855 --> 00:03:51,481
MY LOCATION--SICK BAY.

48
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:52,816
QUARTERLY PHYSICAL CHECK.

49
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,152
OH! WHEW!

50
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:57,445
JUST A FEW SECONDS MORE.

51
00:03:57,571 --> 00:04:00,240
JUST A FEW SECONDS MORE.

52
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:01,575
[MUTTERING]

53
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:03,952
[GROANING]

54
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:07,706
THAT'S A BOY.
KEEP IT UP.

55
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:10,167
WORK OFF A LITTLE SWEAT,
DO YOU GOOD.

56
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,252
KILLIN' ME.

57
00:04:14,046 --> 00:04:16,131
[GROANING]

58
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:21,553
OHH! YOU'RE KILLING ME.

59
00:04:25,515 --> 00:04:26,892
STOP.

60
00:04:27,017 --> 00:04:29,811
OH! AH.

61
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:31,354
WINDED?

62
00:04:31,479 --> 00:04:35,859
YOU'D BE THE LAST
ONE I'D TELL.

63
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,536
KIRK HERE.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

64
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,580
HAVE A LOOK AT THIS,
CAPTAIN.

65
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:57,256
WHAT'S THAT?

66
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,215
UNDETERMINED.

67
00:04:58,339 --> 00:04:59,800
WHATEVER IT IS,
IT'S BLOCKING OUR WAY.

68
00:04:59,925 --> 00:05:01,843
WHEN WE MOVE,
IT MOVES AS WELL.

69
00:05:01,969 --> 00:05:03,303
A VESSEL OF SOME KIND?

70
00:05:03,428 --> 00:05:05,764
NEGATIVE.
MORE SOME TYPE OF DEVICE.

71
00:05:05,889 --> 00:05:07,891
I'LL BE RIGHT UP.

72
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,851
YOU COULD SEE
THE ALARM LIGHTS

73
00:05:09,977 --> 00:05:10,978
FLASHING FROM THERE,
McCOY.

74
00:05:11,103 --> 00:05:12,312
WHY DIDN'T YOU
TELL ME?

75
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,730
FINALLY FINISHED
A PHYSICAL ON YOU,
DIDN'T I?

76
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:17,985
WHAT AM I, A DOCTOR
OR A MOON SHUTTLE CONDUCTOR?

77
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:20,279
IF I JUMPED EVERY TIME
A LIGHT CAME ON
AROUND HERE,

78
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:23,364
I'D END UP
TALKING TO MYSELF.

79
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:24,866
Man on P.A.:
ALL DECKS ALERT.

80
00:05:24,992 --> 00:05:27,577
[SIREN]

81
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:29,621
ALL DECKS ALERT.

82
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,717
BRIDGE.

83
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:48,431
CAPTAIN TO BRIDGE.
Spock: SPOCK HERE.

84
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:49,850
ANY CHANGES?
NEGATIVE.

85
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:52,351
WHATEVER IT IS,
IT SEEMS TO WANT
TO JUST HOLD US HERE.

86
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:54,521
ANY INDICATION OF DANGER
FROM IT?

87
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:55,189
NEGATIVE.

88
00:05:55,314 --> 00:05:56,982
I'LL CHANGE FIRST, THEN.

89
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:59,651
CAPTAIN OUT.

90
00:06:00,861 --> 00:06:04,739
ALL DECKS HAVE
REPORTED GREEN,
MR. BAILEY.

91
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,491
YES, SIR.

92
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:08,994
AND WHEN THE CAPTAIN
ARRIVES, HE'LL EXPECT
A FULL REPORT ON--

93
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:10,411
THE CUBE'S RANGE
AND POSITION.

94
00:06:10,537 --> 00:06:12,455
I'LL HAVE IT BY THEN.

95
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:14,541
RAISING MY VOICE
BACK THERE

96
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,252
DOESN'T MEAN I WAS SCARED
OR COULDN'T DO MY JOB.

97
00:06:17,376 --> 00:06:19,213
IT MEANS I HAPPEN
TO HAVE A HUMAN THING

98
00:06:19,338 --> 00:06:20,755
CALLED AN ADRENALINE GLAND.

99
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:23,382
HMM. IT DOES SOUND MOST
INCONVENIENT, HOWEVER.

100
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,011
HAVE YOU CONSIDERED
HAVING IT REMOVED?

101
00:06:26,845 --> 00:06:28,972
VERY FUNNY.

102
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,183
YOU TRY TO CROSS
BRAINS WITH SPOCK,

103
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:34,602
HE'LL CUT YOU TO
PIECES EVERY TIME.

104
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:38,273
CAPTAIN TO BRIDGE.

105
00:06:38,397 --> 00:06:39,316
SPOCK HERE.

106
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,235
ANY SIGNS OF LIFE?
NEGATIVE.

107
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,777
HAVE YOU TRIED ALL
HAILING FREQUENCIES?

108
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:44,946
AFFIRMATIVE. NO ANSWER
FROM THE CUBE.

109
00:06:45,072 --> 00:06:46,531
HAVE THE DEPARTMENT HEADS
MEET ME ON THE BRIDGE.

110
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:48,449
ALREADY STANDING BY.

111
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:02,256
[BEEPING]

112
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:13,474
REPORTING, SIR.
SENSORS SHOW
IT IS SOLID,

113
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,018
BUT ITS COMPOSITION
IS UNKNOWN TO US.

114
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,437
LIEUTENANT UHURA?

115
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:19,398
HAILING FREQUENCIES
STILL OPEN, SIR.

116
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:21,649
I GET NO MESSAGE
FROM IT.

117
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,324
NAVIGATION.

118
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:32,452
DISTANCE FROM US--
1,593 METERS,

119
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:34,537
POSITION CONSTANT.

120
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:37,707
EACH OF ITS EDGES
MEASURES 107 METERS.

121
00:07:37,832 --> 00:07:40,252
MASS, A LITTLE UNDER
11,000 METRIC TONS.

122
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:41,669
SCOTTY.

123
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:43,546
MODE OF POWER?

124
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:45,424
BEATS ME WHAT
MAKES IT GO.

125
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:47,134
I'LL BUY
SPECULATION.

126
00:07:47,259 --> 00:07:48,843
I'D SELL IT
IF I HAD ANY.

127
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,804
THAT'S A SOLID CUBE.

128
00:07:50,929 --> 00:07:53,223
HOW SOMETHING LIKE THAT
CAN SENSE US COMING,

129
00:07:53,348 --> 00:07:56,017
BLOCK US,
MOVE WHEN WE MOVE,
IT BEATS ME.

130
00:07:56,143 --> 00:07:58,228
THAT'S MY REPORT.

131
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:01,064
LIFE SCIENCES.

132
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,565
SAME REPORT.

133
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:05,402
SIR, WE GOING TO JUST
LET IT HOLD US HERE?

134
00:08:05,526 --> 00:08:06,611
WE'VE GOT PHASER WEAPONS.

135
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:07,988
I VOTE WE BLAST IT.

136
00:08:08,113 --> 00:08:10,698
I'LL KEEP THAT IN MIND,
MR. BAILEY,

137
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:13,201
WHEN THIS BECOMES
A DEMOCRACY.

138
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:24,421
CAPTAIN'S LOG,
STARDATE 1513.8.

139
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,381
STAR MAPS REVEAL
NO INDICATION

140
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,549
OF HABITABLE
PLANETS NEARBY.

141
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:31,511
ORIGIN AND PURPOSE
OF THE CUBE
STILL UNKNOWN.

142
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:35,223
WE'VE BEEN HERE,
HELD MOTIONLESS,
FOR 18 HOURS.

143
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:37,309
ANYTHING FURTHER,
GENTLEMEN?

144
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:40,728
I BELIEVE IT ADDS UP
TO EITHER ONE OF
TWO POSSIBILITIES.

145
00:08:42,314 --> 00:08:46,485
FIRST, A SPACE BUOY
OF SOME KIND.

146
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,278
SECOND?

147
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:51,156
FLYPAPER.

148
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,618
AND YOU DON'T RECOMMEND
STICKING AROUND.

149
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:58,413
NEGATIVE.
IT WOULD MAKE US
APPEAR TOO WEAK.

150
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:01,958
IT'S TIME FOR ACTION,
GENTLEMEN.

151
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:04,544
MR. BAILEY--

152
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:05,504
BRIDGE TO PHASER
GUN CREW--

153
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,381
COUNTERMAND.

154
00:09:07,506 --> 00:09:08,340
I'LL SELECT
WHAT KIND OF ACTION,
MR. BAILEY--

155
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:09,424
I'M SORRY, SIR.
I THOUGHT--

156
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:11,301
ARE YOU EXPLAINING,
MR. BAILEY?

157
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:13,094
I HAVEN'T REQUESTED
AN EXPLANATION.

158
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,596
NOW, AS I WAS ABOUT
TO SAY, NAVIGATOR,

159
00:09:15,722 --> 00:09:17,974
PLOT US A SPIRAL COURSE
AWAY FROM THE CUBE.

160
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:19,351
YES, SIR.

161
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:20,643
WE'LL TRY PULLING
AWAY FROM IT.

162
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:22,479
YES, SIR.

163
00:09:22,603 --> 00:09:24,272
HELMSMAN
TO ENGINE ROOM,

164
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:25,648
STAND BY.

165
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:27,150
ALL DECKS ALERT.

166
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:29,403
WE'RE GOING TO
TRY PULLING AWAY.

167
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,871
COURSE PLOTTED
AND LAID IN, SIR.

168
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,504
ENGAGE, MR. SULU,
QUARTER SPEED.

169
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:49,714
.25, SIR.

170
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,597
STILL BLOCKING US, SIR.

171
00:09:57,722 --> 00:09:59,891
LET'S SEE IF IT'LL GIVE WAY.

172
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:02,060
AHEAD, HALF SPEED.

173
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:04,604
.50, SIR.

174
00:10:26,126 --> 00:10:29,003
RADIATION FROM THE SHORT
END OF THE SPECTRUM INCREASING.

175
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:30,797
ALL STOP, FULL POSITION.

176
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:42,058
IT'S STILL
COMING TOWARD US.

177
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:45,186
RANGE 190 METERS.

178
00:10:53,278 --> 00:10:55,322
RADIATION INCREASING.

179
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:56,906
POWER ASTERN,
HALF SPEED.

180
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:59,493
HALF SPEED.

181
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,251
RADIATION NEARING
THE TOLERANCE LEVEL.

182
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,002
STILL COMING.

183
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,629
GAINING ON US.

184
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,255
ENGINES ASTERN,
FULL SPEED.

185
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,174
FULL SPEED.

186
00:11:31,316 --> 00:11:34,152
RANGE--125 METERS NOW.

187
00:11:39,407 --> 00:11:42,035
HELM, GIVE US WARP SPEED.

188
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,828
WARP ONE, SIR.

189
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:46,206
RADIATION AT
THE TOLERANCE LEVEL.

190
00:11:46,331 --> 00:11:48,667
WARP TWO, SIR.

191
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:57,384
SPEED IS NOW
WARP THREE.

192
00:11:57,509 --> 00:11:59,386
RADIATION PASSING
THE TOLERANCE LEVEL,

193
00:11:59,511 --> 00:12:00,887
ENTERING LETHAL ZONE.

194
00:12:01,012 --> 00:12:03,139
RANGE--51 METERS
AND STILL CLOSING, SIR.

195
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:05,392
PHASER CREW STAND READY.

196
00:12:05,517 --> 00:12:08,520
PHASER CREW
REPORTS READY, SIR.

197
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,285
GROWING. WE CAN TAKE
ONLY A FEW MORE
SECONDS OF THIS.

198
00:12:24,411 --> 00:12:25,953
LOCK PHASERS ON TARGET.

199
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:30,667
MR. BAILEY, LOCK PHASERS!

200
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:33,127
PHASERS LOCKED
ON TARGET, SIR.

201
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:35,422
AT POINT-BLANK RANGE
AND CLOSING.

202
00:12:35,547 --> 00:12:37,257
FIRE MAIN PHASERS.

203
00:12:56,859 --> 00:13:00,530
CAPTAIN'S LOG,
STARDATE 1514.0.

204
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:02,616
THE CUBE HAS BEEN
DESTROYED.

205
00:13:02,741 --> 00:13:05,118
SHIP'S DAMAGE--MINOR.

206
00:13:05,243 --> 00:13:07,078
BUT MY NEXT
DECISION--MAJOR.

207
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:09,038
PROBE ON AHEAD
OR TURN BACK.

208
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,249
NOTHING, CAPTAIN.

209
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:14,669
NO CONTACTS, NO OBJECTS
IN ANY DIRECTION.

210
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:16,588
CARE TO SPECULATE
ON WHAT WE'LL FIND

211
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:18,005
IF WE GO ON AHEAD?

212
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:19,674
SPECULATE?

213
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:23,010
NO.

214
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:25,138
LOGICALLY, WE'LL DISCOVER
THE INTELLIGENCE

215
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:27,056
WHICH SENT OUT THE CUBE.

216
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:30,268
INTELLIGENCE
DIFFERENT FROM OURS

217
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:31,894
OR SUPERIOR?

218
00:13:32,019 --> 00:13:32,853
PROBABLY BOTH.

219
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:36,107
AND IF YOU'RE ASKING
THE LOGICAL DECISION
TO MAKE--

220
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,233
NO, I'M NOT.

221
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:38,485
THE MISSION OF
THE<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

222
00:13:38,610 --> 00:13:41,571
IS TO SEEK OUT
AND CONTACT ALIEN LIFE.

223
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:44,823
HAS IT OCCURRED TO YOU

224
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:47,661
THAT THERE'S
A CERTAIN...INEFFICIENCY

225
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:50,580
IN CONSTANTLY
QUESTIONING ME ON THINGS

226
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:52,540
YOU'VE ALREADY MADE UP
YOUR MIND ABOUT?

227
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:55,335
IT GIVES ME
EMOTIONAL SECURITY.

228
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:01,966
NAVIGATOR,
SET A COURSE AHEAD.

229
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:03,217
PLOTTED.

230
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,136
LAID IN, SIR.

231
00:14:06,845 --> 00:14:07,930
ENGAGE.

232
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:09,557
WARP ONE, SIR.

233
00:14:09,683 --> 00:14:11,309
MR. BAILEY--

234
00:14:11,434 --> 00:14:12,644
PHASER CREWS
WERE SLUGGISH.

235
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:14,187
YOU WERE SLOW
IN LOCKING THEM

236
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:15,522
INTO YOUR
DIRECTIONAL BEAM.

237
00:14:15,647 --> 00:14:16,897
HELMSMAN,

238
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:18,399
ENGINEERING DECKS
COULD HAVE BEEN FASTER, TOO.

239
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:20,234
PROGRAM A SERIES
OF SIMULATED ATTACKS

240
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,277
AND EVASION MANEUVERS.

241
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:23,154
KEEP REPEATING
THE EXERCISE

242
